then you  can not achieve a critical mass and the fission chain reaction stops naturaly. A gas core reactor can achieve<br>
this also in the following way.If a gas core reactor overheats<br>
then the gasous nuclear fuel will undergo thermal expansion.<br>
This will decrease the density of the fuel. As a result you will<br>
no longer have a critical mass and the fission chain reaction will stop naturaly on its own.<br>
